Cell.Data: UML Standards Model Compliance for C / C++
Procedure has more than one exit point.
Function does not return a value on all paths.
Local pointer returned in function result.
Pointer not checked for null before use.
Modification of loop counter in loop body.
UR anomaly, variable used before assignment.
Call has execution order dependant side effects.
File does not end with new line.
No brackets to loop body (added by Testbed).
No brackets to then/else (added by Testbed).
Use of obsolete language feature ( use = - ).
Deprecated usage of ++ or -- operators found.
Use of break statement in loop.
Procedure parameter has a type but no identifier.
Ellipsis used in procedure parameter list.
Use of bit field in structure declaration.
Use of banned function or variable.
No default case in switch statement.
Use of shift operator on signed type.
Switch case not terminated with break.
Signed bit field less than 2 bits wide.
Bit field not signed or unsigned int.
More than one of # or ## in a macro.
Name redeclared in another C name space (MR).
Value is not of appropriate type.
Label is not part of switch statement (MR).
Use of bit operator on signed type.
Use of boolean expression in switch.
Use of ## or # in a macro.
A #if has no #endif in the same file.
Assignment operator in RHS of && or ||.
Anonymous bit field used in structure.
Use of 'defined' keyword in macro body.
Class variable declared in class definition.
Use of numeric literal in expression.
Name is used in standard libraries.
Bit field is not octal, hex or suffix u.
No copy constructor for class with pointers.
No assignment operator for class with pointers.
Empty initialisation exprsn in for loop.
Empty increment exprsn in for loop.
For loop initialisation is not simple.
For loop incrementation is not simple.
Name found with length less than ***.
Switch has missing or extra cases.
Class definition not needed in file.
First parameter not on same line as function.
Pointer to function declared without typedef.
Virtual class members need virtual destructor.
* or & not attached to type in declaration.
Switch has only 1 case and default.
Bit field is not unsigned integral.
Default is not last case of switch.
Macro call has wrong number of parameters.
Reuse of struct or class member name.
Non bit field member in bitfield struct.
Operation not appropriate to plain char.
Literal value requires a U suffix.
Widening cast on complex integer expression.
Widening cast on complex float expression.
No cast when ~ or << applied to small types.
#else has no #if, etc in the same file.
Bit operator with floating point operand.
Bit field is not unsigned integral or enum type.
Macro parameter list has leading space.
Declaration of type not in header file.
Inline member has more than *** statements.
Extern declaration is not in header file.
Null character used within a string.
Identifier matches macro name in 31 chars.
Use of ++ or -- on RHS of && or || operator.
Volatile variable accessed on RHS of && or ||.
More than one break or goto statement in loop.
Switch empty default has no comment.
Empty middle expression in for loop.
Inconsistent usage of loop control variable.
No copy constructor for complex destructor.
No assignment operator for complex destrtor.
